01:33.426 --> 01:35.906
It's Jane Hollander.

01:36.429 --> 01:38.409
Very well. And you?

01:38.565 --> 01:40.636
<i>♪ Over and over h'</i>

01:40.800 --> 01:45.146
I was just thinking about those meetings
you were telling me about.

01:49.576 --> 01:52.352
I remember telling my friend
in the fourth grade...

01:52.512 --> 01:54.219
...that my parents weren't in love.

01:54.380 --> 01:56.053
How did you come to that conclusion?

01:56.216 --> 01:59.288
I don't know. I just-- I felt it.

01:59.452 --> 02:00.590
They never fought.

02:00.753 --> 02:03.324
They just didn't talk, really.

02:03.490 --> 02:06.198
Dad went to work. Mom did Mom stuff.

02:06.359 --> 02:08.066
Dad watched wrestling on TV.

02:08.228 --> 02:11.334
Mom would get the neighbor
on the phone and talk for hours.

02:11.931 --> 02:13.740
They just didn't talk to each other.

02:13.900 --> 02:14.901
Yeah.

02:15.068 --> 02:18.675
I don't remember my parents
talking to each other much, either.

02:20.206 --> 02:23.016
I remember,
we would get home from school...

02:23.176 --> 02:24.951
...and my mom would be laying
on the couch...

02:25.111 --> 02:29.025
...asleep with a newspaper
over her face.

02:29.616 --> 02:32.426
And she would get up
and fix us dinner...

02:32.585 --> 02:34.496
...and we were too scared to tell her...

02:34.654 --> 02:39.194
...that there would be newspaper
ink all over her face.

02:41.794 --> 02:46.766
Then after dinner,
she would lay back down on the couch...

02:46.933 --> 02:49.413
...and put the paper back on her face.

02:50.770 --> 02:52.943
- Sounds like she was exhausted.
- Yeah.

02:54.574 --> 02:56.884
I was scared of my mom.

02:57.343 --> 03:01.348
- And now I've turned into her.
- I can relate to that.

03:02.081 --> 03:04.152
Sometimes I scream at the kids...

03:04.317 --> 03:05.887
...like she used to, to us.

03:06.186 --> 03:09.633
I try and figure out,
"Why am I doing that?"

03:10.023 --> 03:11.969
But then I look at them...

03:12.125 --> 03:14.036
...and I think...

03:14.827 --> 03:16.966
...I didn't choose you.

03:19.265 --> 03:20.573
I love you...

03:20.733 --> 03:23.111
...but I didn't choose you.

03:34.881 --> 03:37.828
When he looks at me,
all sees is a chicken-fried steak...

03:37.984 --> 03:40.294
...and a wet hole to squirt himself into.

03:40.653 --> 03:42.223
Do I know the feeling.

03:42.388 --> 03:46.268
I am so glad that you decided to come.

03:46.426 --> 03:47.769
What do you--?

03:47.927 --> 03:49.167
What do you think?

03:49.729 --> 03:51.606
It's interesting.

03:51.764 --> 03:54.244
Do you--? Do you think that
you'll come back?

03:54.400 --> 03:57.142
If I get to write this article,
I'll need to come back.

03:57.303 --> 03:59.374
Interview some of these ladies.

03:59.906 --> 04:01.613
And you really...

04:01.774 --> 04:05.449
...think that Gregory is gonna give you
a chance to write an article?

04:06.312 --> 04:08.588
I think he's considering it.

04:09.415 --> 04:10.758
Well...

04:11.217 --> 04:12.890
...that's great for you.

04:13.152 --> 04:16.565
<i>♪ And you put the load right on me N'</i>

04:33.239 --> 04:34.684
Hey.

04:35.375 --> 04:37.116
Would you mind if I
bummed a smoke?

04:37.277 --> 04:38.381
All right, sure.

04:38.544 --> 04:39.955
Here you go.

04:50.189 --> 04:52.567
Somebody help me!

05:57.724 --> 05:59.431
I thought it was an earthquake.

05:59.592 --> 06:01.230
I could see the smoke from Midtown.

06:01.394 --> 06:02.668
My windows were shaking.

06:08.601 --> 06:10.911
- Oh, sorry.
- Oh, good morning.

06:15.341 --> 06:17.446
- Wasn't a gas leak?
- That's what they thought.

06:17.610 --> 06:20.921
But then cops found dynamite
and fragments from a homemade bomb.

06:21.080 --> 06:23.959
- So not a gas leak.
- Terrorists. That's the thinking.

06:24.117 --> 06:27.291
- But no one can figure out a target.
- How many dead?

06:27.453 --> 06:28.659
At least two.

06:28.821 --> 06:29.993
But...

06:30.490 --> 06:33.699
- But?
- Um, but they're still collecting body parts.

06:33.860 --> 06:35.771
And nobody knows
how many were in there.

06:35.928 --> 06:38.602
- But at least two are dead.
- They found three hands.

06:38.765 --> 06:41.803
Dustin Hoffman lives next door.
Shares a wall with the house.

06:42.668 --> 06:45.547
A bomb seems advanced
for a crazed fan.

06:45.705 --> 06:47.514
Or somebody who
didn't like The Graduate.

06:47.673 --> 06:50.483
- Who didn't like The Graduate?
- I didn't like The Graduate.

06:52.678 --> 06:54.214
Oh, really?

06:54.380 --> 06:55.518
What didn't you like?

06:55.681 --> 06:57.251
I thought it was pretentious.

06:57.417 --> 07:00.728
A male fantasy masked as
a symbol of student revolt.

07:00.887 --> 07:02.594
I didn't buy it.

07:03.556 --> 07:04.591
Fair enough.

07:06.292 --> 07:09.330
See what you can get confirmed.
Find out who owned the building.

07:09.495 --> 07:11.702
Someone with money.
Nicest block in the Village.

07:11.864 --> 07:13.810
Find who lived there,
who wanted who dead.

07:13.966 --> 07:16.378
- Headed there now.
- Rhodes.

07:16.836 --> 07:21.182
Put your tie on. You represent me
out there, and I'm a dapper son of a bitch.

07:21.841 --> 07:23.445
Yes, sir.

07:24.210 --> 07:25.211
Patti.

07:26.412 --> 07:27.652
Yes?

07:29.415 --> 07:32.157
Send Gabe up, will you?
I've got a sidebar for him.

07:32.418 --> 07:33.658
Mm-hm.

07:40.893 --> 07:42.497
We're immortal now, you and me.

07:43.229 --> 07:45.072
I'm proud of you, man.

07:49.435 --> 07:52.609
Hey, Noah,
your smile could be a touch smilier.

07:52.772 --> 07:54.877
Is that a smile or a grimace?

07:55.041 --> 07:56.042
My smile.

07:56.209 --> 07:59.486
Worry about yourself, Sam.
You look like you're trying to pinch a loaf.

07:59.645 --> 08:02.216
All right, just snap your little pictures.

08:03.249 --> 08:04.922
Jane, why don't you scoot up here?

08:05.084 --> 08:07.894
Maybe a pretty blonde
will get him to smile.

08:08.855 --> 08:10.562
Sure.

08:25.338 --> 08:26.681
Perfect.

08:26.839 --> 08:29.581
I might have to give you
a shared photo credit on this one.

08:52.031 --> 08:53.408
Um...

08:53.733 --> 08:55.610
Angie...

08:55.801 --> 08:56.905
...are you okay?

08:57.169 --> 08:58.807
I'm fine. Thank you.

09:02.975 --> 09:05.455
Oh! Damn it, I'm locked in here.

09:06.379 --> 09:08.154
Unh!

09:13.019 --> 09:16.125
Why don't you-- Why don't you
lay down on the couch?

09:16.289 --> 09:19.327
And I'll-- I'll get you a towel
for your forehead.

09:20.793 --> 09:23.296
I'm afraid if I lie down,
I'll get nauseous again.

09:23.462 --> 09:25.271
Do you have a fever?

09:30.236 --> 09:32.443
Angie, are you drinking tansy oil?

09:33.973 --> 09:35.680
How can you tell?

09:37.076 --> 09:38.680
Your pupils.

09:43.649 --> 09:46.789
I can't be away from
Finn and Gregory's phones this long.

09:48.788 --> 09:50.495
Angie.

09:59.365 --> 10:01.038
How much have you had?

10:02.668 --> 10:04.545
I started last night.

10:05.204 --> 10:07.707
I was told to put it in tea...

10:07.873 --> 10:09.477
...and drink it every three hours.

10:09.642 --> 10:11.349
How far along are you?

10:11.510 --> 10:13.581
I'm two weeks late.

10:13.746 --> 10:15.089
But I know I'm pregnant.

10:15.247 --> 10:19.286
- Two weeks? That could just be--
- I've got three kids.

10:19.452 --> 10:21.022
I know.

10:21.387 --> 10:25.199
I'm-- I'm-- I'm sorry.
I thought that Vera was...

10:25.358 --> 10:27.599
...your only child.

10:36.335 --> 10:38.781
I can't have a fourth one.

10:39.372 --> 10:41.181
I just can't.

10:42.508 --> 10:44.715
We are so strapped.

10:46.612 --> 10:48.523
It's my fault.

10:48.681 --> 10:52.026
At Frank's birthday,
I had too many gin and tonics.

10:52.451 --> 10:53.930
Does he know?

10:57.790 --> 11:02.967
The-- The tansy tea
doesn't always work.

11:03.129 --> 11:04.733
And it can damage the baby.

11:04.897 --> 11:07.036
I don't have a lot of options.

11:16.008 --> 11:18.454
Office of Phinneaus Woodhouse.
This is Angie.

11:19.679 --> 11:21.249
Uh-huh.

11:22.581 --> 11:24.322
Of course.

11:33.392 --> 11:34.837
Jane.

11:40.433 --> 11:43.903
A couple hundred words should be fine.
Attagirl, Jane.

11:44.070 --> 11:46.778
The local angle is what I
wanna play more.

11:55.815 --> 11:56.816
Hello.

11:56.982 --> 11:58.586
So, Jane...

11:58.884 --> 12:00.363
...what do you think?

12:02.188 --> 12:03.895
Yes?

12:04.690 --> 12:05.691
Or yes?

12:08.160 --> 12:09.639
- I think...
- Ah...

12:11.097 --> 12:13.202
Yes? Hm?

12:14.533 --> 12:16.012
Or yes?

12:16.635 --> 12:17.807
The first ones.

12:18.404 --> 12:19.815
- These?
- Mm-hm.

12:21.173 --> 12:22.618
Really?

12:23.008 --> 12:25.648
Guess these are
a little too Elvis on stage, huh?

12:26.512 --> 12:27.718
I've got a girl at Saks...

12:27.947 --> 12:29.722
...lets me test drive the trends.

12:30.983 --> 12:32.553
Jane, sit down, please.

12:42.228 --> 12:44.902
You're a big brain in a pretty
little package, aren't you?

12:47.166 --> 12:49.578
I talked to Finn about your idea...

12:49.735 --> 12:51.772
...about an article on the bra burners.

12:51.937 --> 12:54.679
- Oh, well, it wouldn't exactly be just--
- I know, I know.

12:55.074 --> 12:57.680
The whole thing, the women's march...

12:57.843 --> 13:00.414
...wives refusing to cook dinner
for their husbands.

13:00.579 --> 13:03.719
Gloria Steinem, Phyllis Schlafly,
my mother.

13:03.883 --> 13:05.487
Who's your mother?

13:05.651 --> 13:07.995
Heh, heh. I'm kidding.

13:08.187 --> 13:09.495
Ah...

13:09.722 --> 13:11.395
Anyway, it's great.

13:12.658 --> 13:13.728
Really?

13:14.160 --> 13:15.230
We love it.

13:15.394 --> 13:17.772
It's relevant.
Time isn't covering it.

13:17.930 --> 13:20.968
You know, Newsweek did
a cover story called "Women in Revolt."

13:21.133 --> 13:22.373
Did big numbers for them.

13:23.102 --> 13:25.912
Over 50 percent of our readers
are women. Did you know that?

13:26.071 --> 13:27.948
I did. I did know that.

13:28.107 --> 13:29.245
So the question is...

13:29.875 --> 13:31.855
...who are we gonna get
to write the thing?

13:32.011 --> 13:33.081
We think you're right.

13:33.512 --> 13:37.961
A man's byline, it just makes
the whole story feel disingenuous.

13:38.117 --> 13:39.152
So...

13:39.318 --> 13:41.195
...Finn reached out to Ruth Penney.

13:44.156 --> 13:46.602
- She writes for BusinessWeek.
- Freelancer.

13:46.759 --> 13:48.238
<i>BusinessWeek, Good Housekeeping.</i>

13:49.862 --> 13:51.739
Oh, okay.

13:52.264 --> 13:54.210
Well, I'm glad it's getting written.

13:54.366 --> 13:56.243
Thanks to you.

13:56.402 --> 14:00.145
Now, I told her that if she needs
any help with research, I've got the girl.

14:00.306 --> 14:01.614
This is her number.

14:01.774 --> 14:05.722
I want you to call her, introduce yourself,
see if you can help.

14:07.279 --> 14:08.883
Thank you.

14:11.150 --> 14:13.630
Keep those juices flowing, Jane.

14:13.786 --> 14:16.892
Any time that you have an idea
that you wanna share...

14:17.056 --> 14:19.002
...you come see me. Hm?

14:20.159 --> 14:22.161
You're very special.

14:36.876 --> 14:39.618
Use your own trash can, please.

14:58.597 --> 15:01.043
What's the square footage?

15:01.700 --> 15:04.510
Wow, that must be nice.

15:04.670 --> 15:09.415
And how many units in the building
can Mr. Wilkerson rent out?

15:11.810 --> 15:14.120
Oh, okay, thank you so much.

15:20.452 --> 15:24.366
Well, of course a woman from outside
the magazine has more experience.

15:24.523 --> 15:28.335
How are we supposed to get experience
from inside this magazine?

15:28.494 --> 15:32.135
I cannot believe you pitched an article
about the women's movement.

15:32.298 --> 15:35.745
- I told you I was writing that article.
- I know. I just thought--

15:35.901 --> 15:39.405
You thought you'd undercut me and
steal my article. That's what you thought.

15:39.571 --> 15:43.451
No, it wasn't like that.
I was with Gregory...

15:43.776 --> 15:45.312
...and it just happened.

15:46.078 --> 15:47.318
It just happened?

15:47.479 --> 15:50.358
Okay, I-- I don't know
what's going on here...

15:50.516 --> 15:54.430
...but, Patti, what if a female writer
on a cover piece...

15:54.586 --> 15:56.827
...hurts our EEOC complaint?

15:56.989 --> 16:00.027
I mean, even if she's not from inside?

16:00.392 --> 16:02.838
I don't know.
We'll have to ask Eleanor that.

16:02.995 --> 16:04.065
Who's that?

16:04.229 --> 16:05.606
She's our lawyer.

16:06.231 --> 16:07.403
I'll ask her.

16:08.600 --> 16:10.341
Are you saying...?

16:10.502 --> 16:12.004
I'm in.

16:12.471 --> 16:13.472
Jane.

16:14.206 --> 16:15.583
That's great.

16:15.741 --> 16:17.277
It is great.

16:17.609 --> 16:18.679
Oh, God.

16:21.246 --> 16:22.623
Oh, it's just you.

16:23.415 --> 16:25.053
Girls, Jane is in.

16:26.385 --> 16:27.625
We're out.

16:27.886 --> 16:28.956
- What?
- No, you're not.

16:29.121 --> 16:31.692
- Why are you out?
- Naomi was talking to Eleanor--

16:31.857 --> 16:33.700
Why was Naomi talking to Eleanor?

16:33.859 --> 16:36.567
She needed legal advice
about something else.

16:36.729 --> 16:38.606
Then they talked about the complaint.

16:39.131 --> 16:41.543
Eleanor said now that we've
reached critical mass...

16:41.800 --> 16:44.280
...she's going to start planning
the press conference.

16:44.436 --> 16:46.211
She never mentioned
a press conference.

16:46.372 --> 16:48.318
- Why a press conference?
- Exactly.

16:48.474 --> 16:50.681
She wants to turn us
into a public spectacle.

16:50.843 --> 16:53.551
Our picture would be taken,
our names will be in the paper.

16:53.712 --> 16:55.487
We didn't know
this would be so public.

16:55.647 --> 16:58.059
We're supposed to cover the news,
not make the news.

16:58.217 --> 16:59.321
So Naomi is out too?

16:59.485 --> 17:01.590
- And Diane.
- Oh...

17:01.754 --> 17:04.530
Look, maybe if another magazine
ends up suing and winning...

17:04.690 --> 17:06.863
...then things will change for us too.

17:07.026 --> 17:08.436
We won't have to risk as much.

17:08.761 --> 17:10.468
Anyway, busy day.

17:14.665 --> 17:16.906
- What firm is your lawyer with?
- The ACLU.

17:17.069 --> 17:21.108
- How much do you know about her?
- Well, she's wonderful, normally.

17:21.272 --> 17:24.049
L-- I would consider her a friend. Um...

17:24.209 --> 17:26.119
God, she's-- She's pregnant.

17:26.412 --> 17:28.892
- She's black.
- Met at a consciousness raising meeting.

17:29.048 --> 17:31.585
- Yes.
- How long has she been practicing law?

17:33.385 --> 17:35.661
Where did she get her degree?

17:37.589 --> 17:39.330
How many cases has she tried?

17:44.830 --> 17:46.810
Just a list of the most recent bombings.

17:46.965 --> 17:48.808
- Just in New York or?
- Just in New York.

17:50.135 --> 17:52.342
I thought of you.
Don't you live in the Village?

17:53.505 --> 17:54.506
I do.

17:56.008 --> 17:57.544
Yeah, I do live in the Village.

17:57.709 --> 17:58.847
Felt like...

17:59.011 --> 18:02.891
...a gun going off in my apartment,
but it was about eight blocks away.

18:03.782 --> 18:06.729
I actually thought of you too.

18:08.787 --> 18:13.202
I remember you saying
you were a chocolate person.

18:14.493 --> 18:17.804
Or that you like chocolates.

18:20.265 --> 18:23.337
Thank you.
That's-- That's so very nice.

18:24.169 --> 18:26.308
I'll get on this.

18:36.682 --> 18:39.060
I mean, he keeps
wanting me to make calls.

18:39.218 --> 18:41.391
If he can't handle
a friendly dinner party...

18:41.553 --> 18:43.658
...then what job can I
recommend him for?

18:43.822 --> 18:45.927
Well, don't give up. He's a friend.

18:46.225 --> 18:47.397
He's a source.

18:49.495 --> 18:50.997
Okay, let's get going.

18:51.163 --> 18:53.109
See if that pouch from D.C. has arrived.

18:53.265 --> 18:55.370
Mike sent me
some freeze-dried ice cream...

18:55.534 --> 18:58.981
...from the Air and Space Museum.
New flavor: Mint chocolate chip.

18:59.138 --> 19:02.278
- Want to try some?
- No, thanks. I'll see you later?

19:02.908 --> 19:04.319
Sure.

19:15.554 --> 19:16.555
Hi.

19:19.024 --> 19:20.196
Hi.

19:22.327 --> 19:24.773
I was hoping we could talk about
your conversation...

19:24.930 --> 19:26.967
...about a certain press conference.

19:27.699 --> 19:29.770
So you're a part of it now?

19:29.935 --> 19:33.212
I was hoping to be, but I heard
a lot of girls are dropping out...

19:33.372 --> 19:34.749
...like you.

19:34.907 --> 19:37.285
And I wanted to hear your side.

19:37.442 --> 19:40.150
- Look, I have bigger things going on.
- Like what?

19:40.312 --> 19:43.987
- Like personal life things.
- Like what?

19:44.149 --> 19:46.186
Is your son okay?

19:47.052 --> 19:48.429
Is your husband okay?

19:50.722 --> 19:52.668
I'm about to lose our apartment...

19:52.824 --> 19:55.964
...and the bank won't let me refinance
without Brian's signature.

19:56.128 --> 19:57.835
Obviously, they know he's overseas.

19:57.996 --> 20:00.237
Still need an authorization form.

20:00.399 --> 20:01.901
And I keep sending it...

20:02.067 --> 20:06.140
...but the truck carrying the mail
to the base got blown up twice.

20:07.072 --> 20:10.747
They can't keep you out of your home
because you can't get something signed.

20:10.909 --> 20:13.515
They definitely can.

20:13.679 --> 20:16.023
Well, let's do something about it, then.

20:18.150 --> 20:19.322
Why?

20:20.352 --> 20:22.593
Because that's not right.

20:32.231 --> 20:33.676
Hi, Ned.

20:34.199 --> 20:36.475
Hey, how's it going?

20:37.169 --> 20:40.173
Um, I just brought you these captions.

20:40.339 --> 20:42.842
Great, thanks.

20:50.849 --> 20:52.795
Look at this Qaddafi guy.

20:52.951 --> 20:54.191
What a bozo.

20:54.820 --> 20:57.562
It's like he saw the movie Bullitt,
and said to himself:

20:57.723 --> 21:00.670
"I'm gonna be the Steve McQueen
of Northern Africa."

21:04.930 --> 21:06.170
Um...

21:08.567 --> 21:10.808
Alex's girl left.

21:11.637 --> 21:15.312
So I volunteered to be his researcher.

21:19.244 --> 21:21.417
That's probably for the best.

21:26.351 --> 21:27.887
Uh...

21:28.854 --> 21:30.492
Kathy...

21:30.656 --> 21:34.103
...has offered to take over captions.

21:34.259 --> 21:36.034
If that's okay with you.

21:36.461 --> 21:37.565
<i>Yeah , Kathy“ be fine.</i>

21:37.729 --> 21:40.266
I think-- I think she'll be good.

21:44.536 --> 21:46.379
Well, um...

21:47.873 --> 21:49.546
...goodbye.

21:52.144 --> 21:53.589
Bye.

21:59.184 --> 22:02.290
I'll probably see you
at the vending machines in a little while.

22:05.657 --> 22:09.469
Hello, reporting for duty,
if you'll have me.

22:35.053 --> 22:36.054
Joe.

22:36.421 --> 22:37.661
