You like French toast? How do
I not know if you like French Toast?

41:54.011 --> 41:55.752
That sounds really good...

41:55.913 --> 41:59.258
...but I think, if you don't need me...

41:59.416 --> 42:01.362
...I'm gonna head out.

42:01.519 --> 42:05.763
Catch up on sleep
in my own crappy bed.

42:07.591 --> 42:09.002
Yeah.

42:09.793 --> 42:11.397
I'll see you tomorrow.

42:12.062 --> 42:14.872
Yeah, I'll see you tomorrow.

42:38.455 --> 42:40.799
Sorry, we're not in a rush.

42:40.958 --> 42:43.029
Drive carefully, please.

42:48.732 --> 42:51.178
Cindy, can I ask you something?

42:51.835 --> 42:53.473
Of course.

42:54.538 --> 42:56.950
What have you girls been up to?

42:57.675 --> 42:59.245
That day by the copier.

42:59.410 --> 43:01.583
I see you meet in the bathroom.

43:06.483 --> 43:09.123
We are suing the magazine...

43:10.888 --> 43:12.526
...for the right...

43:12.690 --> 43:14.863
...to be reporters.

43:15.759 --> 43:20.139
It's illegal that they to tell us
we can only work in the pit.

43:47.891 --> 43:49.768
What'd you get?

43:50.628 --> 43:53.108
- Just a harmless Twinkie.
- Ha, ha.

43:53.864 --> 43:56.504
- Want one?
- Sure. Thank you.

43:58.669 --> 44:00.876
- You wanna hear something ironic?
- Mm-hm.

44:01.338 --> 44:03.045
We paid for it with my money.

44:04.274 --> 44:07.118
We used my inheritance
from my grandma for the down payment.

44:07.478 --> 44:11.688
Then the bank would only put
the mortgage in Brian's name.

44:15.586 --> 44:18.260
I know where your name would count.

44:24.194 --> 44:25.901
<i>Okay-</i>

44:26.230 --> 44:27.265
Yeah, I'm in.

44:27.665 --> 44:29.941
- Really?
- Yes.

44:32.136 --> 44:33.410
- Ah.
-om

44:33.570 --> 44:34.674
Hi, there.

44:34.838 --> 44:38.547
- Hi.
- Hi, I'm looking for the, uh, transport desk.

44:38.709 --> 44:41.781
- We're the transport desk. I'll take that.
- And I'll take this.

44:41.945 --> 44:43.754
Sign right there.

44:44.782 --> 44:46.261
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

44:51.455 --> 44:52.456
Oh, my goodness.

44:52.623 --> 44:55.763
That envelope looks like
it fought for our country.

44:56.093 --> 44:59.700
This is it.
Look there, it's where he signed it.

45:00.631 --> 45:02.975
His hand must have been dirty.

45:31.695 --> 45:32.935
Robinson.

45:34.732 --> 45:36.609
Do you know it's dangerous
to walk alone?

45:36.767 --> 45:38.178
Blowing shit up around here.

45:38.669 --> 45:40.205
Yeah, I read about that.

45:40.871 --> 45:44.444
- Get in.
- No, I like the fresh air, so...

45:46.276 --> 45:47.846
Really?

45:48.512 --> 45:50.583
Smells like garbage.

46:02.693 --> 46:06.436
Raymond,
Perry and West 4th Street, please.

46:12.236 --> 46:14.580
So I didn't make it
to the club the other night.

46:14.738 --> 46:16.217
How was it?

46:18.242 --> 46:19.721
Sweaty.

46:20.778 --> 46:22.519
And...

46:22.679 --> 46:24.056
...all encompassing.

46:24.214 --> 46:26.490
But I don't think...

46:26.650 --> 46:30.359
...I learned anything new about jazz.

46:34.458 --> 46:37.928
What do you suppose
would've happened if I had shown up?

46:39.129 --> 46:42.201
- We would have talked about music.
- Sure.

46:43.467 --> 46:45.071
You would have ordered a Scotch.

46:45.235 --> 46:47.408
I would have ordered...

46:47.971 --> 46:50.281
...beer and some wings.

46:50.440 --> 46:52.579
You would have offered to expense it.

46:52.743 --> 46:54.518
Well, I'm good like that.

46:55.946 --> 47:00.691
I would've gone to the ladies' room and
realized I had barbecue sauce on my face.

47:01.819 --> 47:04.265
That sounds like a delightful night.

47:04.822 --> 47:06.426
Yeah, you missed out.

47:07.357 --> 47:10.304
Patti, I want to apologize
for standing you up.

47:15.165 --> 47:18.840
You know, my, uh--
My oldest daughter Lydia...

47:19.369 --> 47:21.280
...she always got her nose in a book.

47:21.438 --> 47:24.317
Likes to make believe
she's from another time and place.

47:24.474 --> 47:27.614
Called me a foulmouthed hooligan
the other day.

47:28.245 --> 47:31.158
My youngest, she's a sponge.

47:31.448 --> 47:34.429
Takes in everything around her.
Always asking questions.

47:34.585 --> 47:36.724
"Why, Dad? Why and how?"

47:37.688 --> 47:39.895
She's sharp as a tack.

47:40.624 --> 47:43.730
She's kind of a Patti Robinson type.

47:43.894 --> 47:46.932
I shouldn't have given you that ticket.

47:47.097 --> 47:50.010
That was inappropriate. I just, ah...

47:51.501 --> 47:52.878
I like talking to you.

47:53.036 --> 47:54.037
I-

47:54.204 --> 47:55.945
...like how you think.

47:56.106 --> 47:57.551
I admire it.

47:57.708 --> 47:59.278
That's good.

47:59.676 --> 48:03.681
Because I'll tell you, I-- I wanna be
a guy that Patti Robinson admires.

48:05.682 --> 48:08.492
And it wasn't wrong of you
to offer me that ticket.

48:08.819 --> 48:10.594
It was wrong of me to take it.

48:12.222 --> 48:14.259
Then why did you?

48:17.728 --> 48:19.730
I'm not a saint.

48:41.084 --> 48:42.961
For the record.

48:43.287 --> 48:46.393
I hoped you weren't a saint.

